snippet.textDisplay:
Here my interpretation.

The first thing that happens in the song is that Marty goes to rehab/therapy to get help. Then it tells us about how he started the abuse. He didn’t think he would get hooked (cheating on his missus and messing up his relationship with himself) he ends up getting addicted/dependent (idk Marty’s entire situation) and he feels like he’s going through hell from needing drugs to survive, withdrawal symptoms, and how it affects his daily life with other people. Many people say that they watch their life being taken away from them. Mel represents his old self, the line “you pulled away when I went in for the kiss” illustrates that he wants to return back to his old life and way of living before the drug abuse. It’s also supported by the line “in a boring conversation with a girl named Mel about a boy in Cincinnati called Marty as well.” He keeps fighting not to go back, but his friends keep him clean. Maybe it’s the only way he can feel like his old self before using, temporarily fixing his brain chemistry if it is messed up.
And the video being centered around be and internet pop culture could mean he is absorbed in surfing/using the internet to make himself feel better. It’s supposed to be a rehab center in the video after all. This doesn’t help the fact he’s in vr though..
Could also be that when he started detoxing he was just surrounded with cravings and thoughts. Wanting it more than he ever had. Maybe the rehab center isn’t a vr world and more of what’s going on in his head; all these things are associated with the internet. His brain might be compensating or panicking without the thing that it had been relying on.

Let me know what you guys think. I really like reading video interpretations and analysis, but I haven’t been seeing much on this video. Maybe you guys all get it and decide to make random jokes instead. 😞
